Package com.adobe.livecycle.rightsmanagement.client

Contains classes that enable you to create client applications that can invoke Document Security service operations.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
AbstractPolicyManager The AbstractPolicyManager interface defines a mechanism to register abstract policies with the Rights Management service and to search and modify abstract policies that are already registered.Administrator accounts can register, search, and modify all abstract policies.
DocumentManager The DocumentManager interface provides methods for manipulating the policy security of documents.
EventManager The EventManager interface enables you to search for events.
ExternalUserManager The ExternalUserManager interface provides methods for managing external users.
LicenseManager The LicenseManager interface provides methods for retrieving and manipulating document licenses and for retrieving information about licenses from the server.
PolicyManager The PolicyManager interface defines a mechanism to register policies with the Rights Management service and to search and modify policies that are already registered.
RightsManagementEncryptionService RightsManagementEncryptionService interface provides methods to protect, unprotect, and inspect documents.
RightsManagementReaderExtensionService RightsManagementReaderExtensionService interface provides methods Reader Extending a DRM-protected document.
WatermarkManager The WatermarkManager interface provides methods for creating, manipulating, retrieving, and removing watermarks.
 

Class Summary
RightsManagementClient Enables you to create Java objects that can invoke operations supported by the Rights Management service.
RightsManagementClient2 Enables you to create Java objects that can invoke operations supported by the Client Encryption service.
 

Package com.adobe.livecycle.rightsmanagement.client Description

Contains classes that enable you to create client applications that can invoke Document Security service operations.
